
commands:

 plotting commands are available in the shell window by refering to instance
 "plot". For example

 Matplotlib commands:

   plot.set_xlabe( "velocity (mm/s)" )
   plot.set_ylabel( "Intensity (counts)" )
   plot.set_title( "A spectrum" )
   
 Histogram plotting command:
  
  For 2-D plot:

   plot.replot( SQEData, min = 0.0 )


1. Launch the gui
2. File -> Open pickled histogram -> Choose "examples/I(vel).pkl" 
3. Click on "plot" tab on the right panel
4. In the command window, type
  plot.set_ylabel( "Intensity(counts)" )
  plot.set_title( "A spectrum" )
5. Click on the "disk" button on the toolbar to save the figure
6. File -> Open pickled histogram -> Choose "examples/spehist.pkl"
7. In the command windoow,
  plot.set_xlim(0,130)
  plot.set_title( "S(phi,E)" )
8. Save the image
9.  File -> Open pickled histogram -> Choose "examples/sqehist.pkl"
  plot.replot(SQEData, min=0)
  plot.set_title("S(Q,E)")
10. Save the image
11. open figures

